      • fsWMis

        public static int[][] fsWMis​(java.lang.String in,
                             java.lang.String lookFor,
                             int misMax)
        Takes a string, in, and looks for a matching substring, lookFor, that may have a number of mismatches in it. Example: in = "applebananaorange" lookFor = "binana" misMax = 1 lookFor is part of in with one mismatch in the second letter of lookFor This method will return int[0][0] = 5 [0][0] is the first case of a match found with allowed number of mismatches = position of first char in String in int[0][1] = 6 [0][1] within this first case found the first mismatch [1] is at position 6 in String in General form of this double array that is returned is int[each instance of a match within allowable mismatches][number of mismatch within String lookFor, not 0] = position in String in not 0 above means 0 in the second bracket of returned int[][], [x][0], indicates the position of the first char of that particular match found. Position begins at 0.
        Parameters:
        in - The string to look in.
        lookFor - The string we are looking for.
        misMax - The maximum number of mismatches within String lookFor.
        Returns:
        int[][] explained in method details.
